  "rationale": "The base style is LOCKED (offGridExpansion=false), so every section is reuse/adapt with a real seededFrom and no off-grid treatments (no stagger/overlap/bleed on non-hero) \u2014 the page earns trust through disciplined alignment. Order: (1) an inverse hero bookend reusing hero-split-media-copy, the ONLY section carrying the brand accent on its display title with the single sanctioned text-on-media + overlap; (2) value-props adapted from features-split-feature, rendering the THREE props as one repeatable feature-item run on the open cream canvas (no boxed cards, obeying no-cards-on-cream); (3) a gallery adapted from gallery-mosaic-with-overflow \u2014 bento maps to the drawable collage archetype, keeping only the flag-independent ghost-word + marginal-caption (dropping the seed's bleed/stagger, which are locked off-grid); (4) social proof mapped onto WoodWave's editorial vocabulary as a testimonial+stat split on a panel (the brand has no logo-wall, so the logos:true request is intentionally NOT rendered \u2014 flagged gap, mapped to quote+stat instead); (5) a centered conversion bookend adapting hero-split-media-copy, with typographic arrow/slash links (no buttons). Centering is used only on the hero and cta stacks per no-centered-everything; every non-hero section stays on surface/primary or panel with no accent, honoring the single-accent rule."
